The 2024 Ford Mustang is a celebrated American sports car known for its performance and iconic design. Available as both a coupe and a convertible, it blends nostalgic styling with modern features. The exterior showcases an aggressive front fascia, sleek body lines, LED headlights, and multiple wheel options from 17 to 20 inches. Inside, the Mustang features a driver-focused cockpit with a digital instrument cluster, a large infotainment screen, and premium materials like leather upholstery in higher trims.

Performance-wise, the 2024 Mustang offers a range of engines to suit different driving preferences. The 2.3L EcoBoost I4 turbocharged engine delivers around 310 horsepower and 350 lb-ft of torque, providing a balance of efficiency and power. For enthusiasts seeking more performance, the 5.0L V8 engine in the Mustang GT produces 450 horsepower and 410 lb-ft of torque, ensuring a thrilling driving experience. Transmission options include a 6-speed manual and a 10-speed automatic, with rear-wheel drive standard across all models.

The Mustang's advanced technology includes driver-assistance features like adaptive cruise control, lane-keeping assist, and a pre-collision system. The SYNC 4 infotainment system supports Apple CarPlay, Android Auto, and has a premium sound system available.
